The article is a transcript of remarks made by the First Lady, Jill Biden, during a tour of the East Room in The White House. She discusses the theme of this year's holiday decorations, which is "Magic, Wonder, and Joy." The rooms in the White House are designed to capture the delight and imagination of children. Each room has a different theme, such as a sweet shop, a recreation of Santa's Workshop, and a celebration of music and merriment. The First Lady also mentions the Gold Star tree, which honors fallen service members, and the official White House Christmas tree, which features ornaments from across the country. She expresses gratitude to the volunteers and decorators who helped bring the holiday spirit to life in the White House. The First Lady ends her remarks by emphasizing the importance of finding hope and healing in difficult times and wishing everyone a Merry Christmas and happy holidays.